== Roasted Chickpeas and Shallots ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Halve,
peel, and cut @shallot{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Toss chickpeas and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp},
half the @Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp} (all for 4), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are golden and tender and shallot is
caramelized, ~{18-20%minutes}. (You'll add more to the sheet after 11 minutes.)

== Tomatoes and Mozzarella ==

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Place tomatoes in a #small bowl{}; toss with @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}
(2 tsp for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}.

== Ciabatta Croutons ==

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} lengthwise; cut into ¾-inch strips. Tear strips into
rough cubes. Transfer to a #large bowl{}; toss with @olive oil{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for
4 servings), @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Once chickpeas and shallot have roasted 11 minutes, remove from oven and push to
one side of baking sheet; carefully add croutons to empty side. (For 4, add
croutons to a second sheet; toast on middle rack.) Return to top rack until
golden and crispy, ~{7-9%minutes}. Wipe out bowl.

Once finished roasting, carefully transfer everything to bowl used to season
croutons to cool.

== Creamy Balsamic Vinaigrette ==

Remove tomatoes from bowl and set aside, leaving marinade behind.

Whisk @mayonnaise{1%tbsp} and @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} into marinade until smooth.
(For 4 servings, use all the mayonnaise and mustard.)

Slowly whisk in @olive oil{4%tbsp} (8 TBSP for 4), drizzling a little bit at a
time, until creamy. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Reserve 1 1/2 TBSP dressing
(3 TBSP for 4) for serving.

== Assembly ==

Add @spinach{5%ounce} to bowl with cooled chickpeas, shallot, and croutons. Toss
with remaining dressing until evenly coated.

Divide salad between plates. Top with mozzarella and tomatoes. Drizzle with
reserved dressing and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to serve.